(2165, 1856, 'how_to_consign_a_master_airwaybill', 'Back to Back shipment\r\n\r\nShipper HTFN member name and address at origin. \r\n\r\nConsignee to be addressed to (if destination is Jakarta) : \r\nPT. CARDIG Logistics Indonesia\r\nT.P.S Taman Soewarna Unit B 3\r\nSoekarno - Hatta International Airport\r\nCengkareng - Tangerang Indonesia\r\nTel. 62-21-559 116 20\r\nFax. 62.21.550.2127 \r\nAtt : Mr. Suryanto\r\n\r\nDeclared as \" Consolidated Shipment as per attached HAWB\" (or manifest if issued)\r\n\r\nFreight must be Prepaid only\r\n\r\nConsolidation Shipment\r\n\r\nShipper, Consignee (same as for back to back shipment)\r\n\r\nDeclare as \" Consolidated Shipment as per attached Manifest\"\r\n\r\nFreight must be prepaid only\r\n'),
(2166, 1856, 'how_to_consign_a_master_b/l', 'Back to Back shipment\r\n\r\nShipper HTFN member name and address at origin.\r\n\r\nConsignee to be addressed to (if destination is Jakarta) :\r\nPT. CARDIG LOGISTICS INDONESIA\r\nHalim Perdana Kusuma Airport\r\nJakarta 13610 - Indonesia\r\nTel. 62-21-8089 0040 - 41\r\nFax. 62.21.808.0048\r\nAtt : Mr. Iswan Izhar\r\n\r\nMark and Number as per shipping instruction and as put on boxes, etc.\r\n\r\nContainer and seal number in case of consolidated / loaded FCL - NVOCC B/L . Express Bill of Lading is recommended.\r\n\r\nFreight to be Prepaid only.\r\n\r\nConsolidation Shipment \r\n\r\nShipper , Consignee (same as back to back shipment) \r\nDeclaration : \" As per attached Statement \" \r\nContainer and seal number, type of container, weight and measurment etc. as normal procedure. \r\nAttached to master B/L a statement with container and seal number, type of container, weight of container, all each individual HB/L with full detail (Number of HB/L , Marks , number of packages , description of goods , weight , measurment) and total packages , weight. \r\nFreight to be prepaid. \r\n'),
(2167, 1856, 'how_to_consign_a_house_airwaybill', 'Never state \"AS AGREED\" to declare the freight. Customs will calculate the duties and taxes based on the higher rates, and they will use rates in MAWB or MBL that higher than the real freight cost.\r\n\r\nShipper, Consignee, etc as per shipping instruction / LC / Purchase order plus telephone number. \r\n\r\nFreight may as Prepaid or Collect, agreed amount of selling rate must be mentioned or confirm by destination agent.\r\n\r\nIn case of Coload Shipment / Consolidation where HAWB use as agent to agent shipping document, freight must be prepaid and the final importer shipping document may as collect. \r\n'),
(2168, 1856, 'how_to_consign_a_house_b/l', 'Never state \"AS AGREED\" to declare the freight. Customs will calculate the duties and taxes based on the higher rates, and they will use rates in MAWB or MBL that higher than the real freight cost.\r\n\r\nShipper, Consignee, etc. as per shipping instruction / LC / Purchase Order plus telepone number. \r\nFreight may as Prepaid or Collect. \r\nIf loaded into a FCL include Container and seal number. \r\n'),
(2169, 1856, 'creating_consolidation_manifest:_air', 'House Manifest form not specified, normal form can be used but please include the following:\r\n\r\nMAWB NUMBER \r\nHAWB NUMBER \r\nPIECES AND WEIGHT \r\nSHIPPER AND CONSIGNEE \r\nFLIGHT AND DEPARTURE DATE \r\nGOODS DESCRIPTION \r\nCOLLECT OR PREPAID \r\n'),
(2170, 1856, 'creating_consolidation_manifest:_ocean', 'Sea Cargo manifest where as form not specified, normal form can be use, include the following information:\r\n\r\nMB/L \r\nPort of Loading \r\nPort of Discharge \r\nConsolidator name \r\nDestination agent name (CARDIG LOGISTICS INDONESIA) \r\nVessel \r\nVoyage \r\nETS/ETA \r\nContainer and seal no. \r\nAll per individual HB/L number \r\nNumber and type of packages \r\nGross weight \r\nMeasurement \r\nDescription of goods \r\nShipper / consignee and notify party full address \r\nFreight prepaid or collect but not the freight amount itself \r\nShipping marks \r\nTotal of package, weight, measurement at the bottom \r\n\r\nThis manifest must be stamped and signed. \r\n'),
(2171, 1856, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_mawb', 'Master Final destination\r\nCargo under Back to Back and Consolidation can only be accepted with Master final destination Jakarta, Surabaya, Semarang and Denpasar where as CARDIG LOGISTICS has its international inbound traffic offices. For other destination within Indonesia, please consult CARDIG LOGISTICS Jakarta office prior shipping arrangement \r\n'),
(2172, 1856, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_mb/l', 'Master Final destination Cargo under Back to Back and Consolidation can only be accepted with Master final destination Jakarta, Surabaya, Semarang and Denpasar where as Cardig Logistics has its international inbound traffic offices. '),
(2173, 1856, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_hawb', 'Please note instruction in \'How to consign a HAWB\' above. '),
(2174, 1856, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_hb/l', 'Please note instructions in \'How to consignee a HB/L\' above. '),
(2175, 1856, 'pre-alert_instructions:_air', 'Pre-advice is a must, earliest or prior to ship and send by any communication method to our Airfreight office fax No. 62-21-550 2127: \r\ne-mail to : suryaboer@cardiglogistics.com, cc to : iswan.nizar@cardiglogistics.com, cc to : asrul@cardiglogistics.com\r\nAn advice must include complete shipping detail;\r\n\r\n\r\nMAWB \r\nHAWB \r\nFlight \r\nDate \r\nPieces \r\nWeight \r\nConsignee \r\nImporter Name and Full Address telephone etc. (PO. Box or Bank Address is not sufficient). \r\n\r\n'),
(2176, 1856, 'pre-alert_instructions:_ocean', 'Pre-Advice is a must, earliest, immediately after shipment and send by any communication method to our Seafreight office fax No. 62-21-8080040-41\r\ne-mail to : iswan.nizar@cardiglogistics.com, cc to : asrul@cardiglogistics.com\r\nAn advice must include complete shipping detail;\r\n\r\n\r\nOBL \r\nHBL \r\nVessel \r\nVoyage \r\nETS \r\nETA \r\nImporter name and full address / telephone , PO. Box or Bank address is not sufficient \r\nShipping agent full address in Indonesia.\r\n\r\nBack to Back Shipments \r\nShipping Document Copies must be sent by any method and received by CARDIG LOGISTICS prior to vessel\'s arrival. Master B/L as Express Bill Of Lading is recommended instead to courier original. \r\n\r\nConsolidation Shipments\r\nShipping Document Copies (complete) must be sent by any method and received by CARDIG LOGISTICS 7 working days prior to vessel\'s arrival. Master B/L as Express Bill Of lading is recommended instead to courier original. \r\n'),
(2177, 1856, 'customs_clearance', 'Indonesian Customs only receives and process the complete docs, means\r\n- Consignee Original Letter of Authority\r\n- Original Airwaybill (Master/House) \r\n- Original Invoices (means with SHIPPER\'S SIGNATURE, SHIPPER\'S COMPANY STAMP, WITH SHIPPER\'S COMPANY HEAD LETTER)\r\n- Consignee must have this following license ; SRP (Customs Registration Letter), API (Importers Identification Number) and NPWP (Company Number Tax Identification)\r\n- Cosignnee must have NPIK (for specific items), POM (for durgs and food)\r\nIt means before you send the cargo to Indonesia, make sure give us alerts in advance so we can check to the consignee whether they have the mention requirement or not.\r\n\r\nOriginal invoice means not sent by fax, not computer generated invoice, and not copies.\r\n\r\n\r\nCARDIG LOGISTICS can arrange permanent customs clearance on behalf of shipper if CARDIG LOGISTICS is mentioned as consignee and or notify party in the shipping and other documents. This mean CARDIG LOGISTICS will acting as importer and all nessesary import permit must be provided by CARDIG LOGISTICS and import duty/tax will be registered under the name and risk of CARDIG LOGISTICS. We would not recommended this practise. In normal case consignee will provide Authorizartion Letter, their Tax Registration Number and Import Lisence.\r\n\r\nAverage clearance time for air freight without physical customs inspection 1-2 days and with customs inspection 2-3 days, for sea freight without inspections 2-3 days and with inspection 3-5 days counted as working days and subject to complete documents without discrepancy(s) on the goods and document(s), to be accepted by Indonesian Authority/regulation. \r\n\r\nOriginal Commercial Invoice must be provided for customs clearance. For airfreight must be attached to the relevant Air Waybill. Failure to comply original, consignee must make a legal statement that invoice value is correct and need customs approval.Please avoid providing only copies.\r\n\r\nCertificate of Analysis is required for chemicals.\r\n\r\nSpecial permits from relevant government department / institution for telecommunication device, any kind of medicine / food / beverage (consider as commercial), and any media materials, also see Tact Rules. \r\n\r\nOriginal passport is required for removal / personal effect goods to get free import duty / tax if Indonesian citizen , plus resident and working permit if non Indonesian citizen.Please contact us before shipping this kind of cargo. \r\n'),
(2178, 1856, 'transshipment_requirements', 'Generally no transhipment facilities, cargo to be customs cleared at port/airport of destination mentioned on Master shipping document. Otherwise importer have to put guarantee 100% of total Import Duty and Tax before onforward to next Indonesian Customs port/airport. '),
