(4096, 1927, 'creating_consolidation_manifest:_air', 'Should be consigned to Transber SAC, including the following information: \r\n\r\nMaster AWB \r\nHouse AWB \r\nCarrier, flight number and date \r\nConsignee including complete company name \r\nNumber of packages and gross weight \r\nDescription of goods \r\nTotal weight and number of packages consolidated'),
(4097, 1927, 'creating_consolidation_manifest:_ocean', 'Must be consigned to Transber SAC including the following information: \r\n\r\nMaster B/L number \r\nHouse B/L number \r\nShipping line information, vessel number and date \r\nConsignee including complete company name \r\nNumber of packages and gross weight \r\nDescription of goods \r\nTotal weight and number of packages consolidated'),
(4098, 1927, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_mawb', 'Creation of Master AWB:\r\n\r\nCorrectly indicate the consignee (including contact information) \r\nExact weight, not to exceed +/- 5% of actual weight of shipment \r\nExact number of packages \r\nFor AIR shipments, description should read simply \"Consolidated as per attached manifest\". '),
(4099, 1927, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_mb/l', 'Creation of Master B/L:\r\n\r\nCorrectly indicate the consignee (including contact information) \r\nExact weight, not to exceed +/- 5% of actual weight of shipment \r\nExact number of packages \r\nFor OCEAN shipments, the description should specify the contents of each House B/L. \r\nFor ocean shipments please also indicate the container number, vessel section number and supervisor number. In case an inspection is required, please indicate shipment conditions for the container (FCL/FCL, LCL/LCL, etc.) '),
(4100, 1927, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_hawb', 'Creation of House AWB, House B/L:\r\n\r\nCorrectly indicate the consignee (including contact information) \r\nExact weight of shipment \r\nExact number of packages \r\nDescription of goods '),
(4101, 1927, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_hb/l', 'Creation of House AWB, House B/L:\r\n\r\nCorrectly indicate the consignee (including contact information) \r\nExact weight, not to exceed +/- 5% of actual weight of shipment \r\nExact number of packages \r\nDescription of goods \r\nFor ocean shipments please indicate the container number, vessel section number and supervisor number. In case an inspection is required, include a notice that the container is exclusively for the listed client. '),
(4102, 1927, 'pre-alert_instructions:_air', 'It is very important to receive pre-alert after arrival of the shipment. Please send a copy of the MAWB/MBL, HAWB/HBL manifest to the following:\r\nFax Number: (511) 572 0269\r\nEmail Addresses: rdiaz@transberperu.com, mmanrrique@transberperu.com, hcordova@transberperu.com'),
(4103, 1927, 'pre-alert_instructions:_ocean', 'In order to verify the information included in the shipping documents and to verify the arrival of cargo we must receive a pre-alert with copies of the M B/L and shipping manifest attached. '),
(4104, 1927, 'customs_clearance', 'We are able to do clearance and delivery for both air and ocean shipments. Peruvian Custom will require the following original documents:\r\n\r\nHB/I or HAWB\r\nCommercial invoice \r\nPacking list \r\nOriginal Certificate of origin, if a trade agreement exists.\r\nPlease provide us information prior to shipping cargo in order to check the necessary paperwork, duties and taxes.'),
(4105, 1927, 'transshipment_requirements', 'Shipping documents must indicate \"Cargo en Transito\" (Master AWB, House AWB, B/L, F B/L and manifest). '),
(4106, 1927, 'legal_requirements_with_regards_to_commercial_invoices,_certificates_of_origin,_etc.', 'The commercial invoice should show the name and address of the shipper, name and address of consignee, invoice number, shipping date and complete description of goods. If the origin country has signed a trade agreement with Peru, a certificate of origin must be issued.'),
(4107, 1927, 'dangerous_goods_requirements', 'Dangerous goods must be sent with a certificate of dangerous cargo. There is a category of goods for which permission must be obtained from the Ministry of Industry before entering Peru. Please contact TRANSBER for additional information.'),
