(4283, 1934, 'how_to_consign_a_house_airwaybill', '- Cnee\'s name and address.\r\n- Phone number, email and contact person. \r\n- Importer\'s CUIT (vat) number (in \"cnee\'s name & address\").\r\n\r\n\r\nRemarks: otherwise customs penalties will be charged.'),
(4284, 1934, 'how_to_consign_a_house_b/l', '- Cnee\'s name and address.\r\n- Phone number, email and contact person. \r\n- Importer\'s CUIT (vat) number (in \"cnee\'s name & address\" or in \"accounting information\").\r\n'),
(4285, 1934, 'creating_consolidation_manifest:_air', '- MAWB number \r\n- HAWB number \r\n- Qty of pieces \r\n- Gross weight (in KG).\r\n- Shipper.\r\n- Cnee\r\n- Nature of goods\r\n- Flight information.'),
(4286, 1934, 'creating_consolidation_manifest:_ocean', '- MBL number \r\n- hbl/s number \r\n- Qty of pieces \r\n- Total Volume (in cbm).\r\n- Gross weight (in KG). '),
(4287, 1934, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_mawb', '- Pls apply freight prepaid.\r\n- Pls always show \"CONSOL SHIPMENT\" in \"nature & qty of goods\".\r\n- Pls show in \"handling information\" if goods need any special care (such as temperature, handling, etc). \r\n- Our CUIT number must be shown in \"handling information\" too.'),
(4288, 1934, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_mb/l', '-Pls always show \"CONSOL SHIPMENT\" in description part.\r\n-description should include NCM number\r\n'),
(4289, 1934, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_hawb', '- Airfreight could be shown as \"as agreed\" but we\'ll need to know amounts of freight, due carrier and due agent in advance in order to submit the info to our Customs.\r\n- Pls show if freight is prepaid or collect.\r\n- Pls show if charges are prepaid or collect.\r\n- Original #2 (for cnee) must come inside a pouch.\r\n- Importer\'s CUIT number and HS code must be shown in \"handling information\".  In case of more than one HS code, the one with the higher value (goods value) must be shown on HAWB.\r\n\r\nRemarks: otherwise customs penalties will be charged.'),
(4290, 1934, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_hb/l', '-hbl can be rated or \"as agreed\"\r\n-description should include NCM number\r\n-Express release of hbls is not allowed by Argentinian customs.'),
(4291, 1934, 'pre-alert_instructions:_air', '- Pls send complete pre-alert (MAWB/HAWB/Manifest/Comm Inv/Packing List/Certifications/Etc) from 24hs to 48hs before the departure (working days).\r\n- We suggest to ask for our green light in order to avoid problems or customs penalties at destination.\r\n- Confirm if original commercial docs will be sent along with the HAWB.\r\n- Pls send your pre-alert to: bueim@lynx.com.ar'),
(4292, 1934, 'pre-alert_instructions:_ocean', 'All new bookings should be informed to us on time, that is previous to start coordination at origin, and previous to any doc deadline. Information should include: \r\n-full booking details: vessel\'s name, deadline, etd, qty, weight, dims, commodity \r\n-shipper\'s full info: name, address, contact info \r\n-cnee\'s full info: name, address, contact info  (so we can contact them and confirm their acceptance of the new shipment) \r\n-carrier\'s info (depending on which carrier you\'ll use, consignation of mbls will be different).\r\n\r\nWe need to see drafts of hbl and mbl, at least 3 days before doc deadline at your side, in order to have them check by all parties here at Bue and receive the confirmation. Pls, send drafts and booking information to our group \"Bue Ocean Imports\": bueocim@lynx.com.ar\r\n-Pre alert should be sent after drafts are confirmed by us.\r\n-original mbls (3) and hbls (3) are needed at destination at least 1 week before vessel arrival (in order to be able to present them to customs). \r\nWe must receive full sets of original mbls (3) by courier from you. \r\ncnee needs to have original hbls before vessel arrival: we may also receive original hbls and be instructed by you to handle them to cnee. Or shipper may send orignal hbls to cnee directly.'),
(4293, 1934, 'customs_clearance', '- Pls kindly note that Lynx Cargo International S.A. cannot act as importer/exporter of HAWB.\r\n- The local company must be duly registered as importer/exporter before our local Customs. '),
(4294, 1934, 'transshipment_requirements', ' '),
(4295, 1934, 'legal_requirements_with_regards_to_commercial_invoices,_certificates_of_origin,_etc.', '- Original commercial invoice, packing list, special certificates (if required) are needed by the local Customs in order to clear goods (customs clearance).  Shipper must always send the original commercial docs. '),
(4296, 1934, 'dangerous_goods_requirements', 'Some DGR goods are not accepted by the Argentinian Customs or have special requirements, which should be checked in advance (before shipping out).'),
(4297, 1934, 'special_instructions', 'Airfreight: all pieces must be properly labeled in order to avoid problems/delays and customs penalties at destination.\r\n\r\nDDU/DDP: do not ship out without our approval, pls contact us in advance. '),
