(5802, 1987, 'how_to_consign_a_master_airwaybill', 'Consigned to our Company as per the details in the HTFN Company directory. (For Transit Cargo additional note has to be mentioned: \"In Transit to ......... via Bangkok\") '),
(5803, 1987, 'how_to_consign_a_master_b/l', 'Consigned to our Company as per the details in the HTFN Company directory. (For Transit Cargo additional note has to be mentioned: \"In Transit to ......... via Bangkok\") '),
(5804, 1987, 'how_to_consign_a_house_airwaybill', 'In general as per the Commercial Documents. \r\nFor shipments in Transit the FINAL destination has to be mentioned \r\nThe HAWB has to be RATED! (Do not mention: \"As Agreed\") \r\nIn order to avoid any kind of mistakes, our partner should first (before the Departure of any cargo) advise the Consignee\'s details (Company Name, Contact Person, Tel, Fax, e-mail and address) and in case on hand also a copy of the HAWB in order for us to double check and confirm back the correctness (some Consignees have different Company names and addresses and they might wish to use their customs card for a specific one). '),
(5805, 1987, 'how_to_consign_a_house_b/l', 'In general as per the Commercial Documents. \r\nFor shipments in Transit the FINAL destination has to be mentioned \r\nIn order to avoid any kind of mistakes, our partner should first (before the Departure of any cargo) advise the Consignee\'s details (Company Name, Contact Person, Tel, Fax, e-mail and address) and in case on hand also a copy of the HB/L in order for us to double check and confirm back the correctness (some Consignees have different Company names and addresses and they might wish to use their customs card for a specific one).'),
