(5812, 1987, 'pre-alert_instructions:_air', 'Copy of HAWB, Commercial Invoice and Manifest to be sent to air.imp@ewas.co.th or fax +66-2-712-0156.\r\nIf possible, please mention also the Contact details of the Consignee (Contact Person, tel, fax, e-mail)'),
(5813, 1987, 'pre-alert_instructions:_ocean', 'Copy of HAWB, Commercial Invoice and Manifest to be sent to seafreight@ewas.co.th or fax +66-2-712-0158. We have to declare final consignee to customs 24 hours before vessel arrival, otherwise customs penalties occur.\r\n'),
(5814, 1987, 'customs_clearance', 'We can do customs clearance for any air and ocean shipments. For DDP shipments please note that we do not advance any Duty/VAT above US$ 250.-/HAWB'),
(5815, 1987, 'transshipment_requirements', 'For MASTER: additional note has to be mentioned: \"In Transit to ......... via Bangkok\" \r\nFor HOUSE: the FINAL destination has to be mentioned \r\nFor MANIFEST: the FINAL destination and \"In Transit to ....... via Bangkok\" has to be mentioned \r\n'),
(5816, 1987, 'legal_requirements_with_regards_to_commercial_invoices,_certificates_of_origin,_etc.', 'Must mention the correct Consignee\'s details (Company, Address etc.):\r\nIn order to avoid any kind of mistakes, our partner should first (before the Departure of any cargo) advise the Consignee\'s details (Company Name, Contact Person, Tel, Fax, e-mail and address) and in case on hand also a copy of the HAWB in order for us to double check and confirm back the correctness (some Consignees have different Company names and addresses and they might wish to use their customs card for a specific one).\r\nPlease note that the value mentioned in the Commercial Invoice is subject to be accepted by the Customs Officers. Any under-valuation might delay the Importation (storage charges may occur) and will cause a penalty fee to be paid. \r\n'),
(5817, 1987, 'dangerous_goods_requirements', 'As per IATA rules and regulations. For DDU and DDP shipments our partner has to advise the Consignee\'s details before the Departure of any cargo (Company Name, Contact Person, Tel, Fax, e-mail and address) in order for us to double check and confirm back the correctness (some Consignees have different Company names and addresses and they might wish to use their customs card for a specific one). '),
