(5868, 1989, 'pre-alert_instructions:_air', 'Pre-advice is a must, earliest or prior to ship and send by any communication method to our Airfreight office fax No. 62-21-550 2127: \r\ne-mail to : suryaboer@cardiglogistics.com, cc to : iswan.nizar@cardiglogistics.com, cc to : asrul@cardiglogistics.com\r\nAn advice must include complete shipping detail;\r\n\r\n\r\nMAWB \r\nHAWB \r\nFlight \r\nDate \r\nPieces \r\nWeight \r\nConsignee \r\nImporter Name and Full Address telephone etc. (PO. Box or Bank Address is not sufficient). \r\n\r\n'),
(5869, 1989, 'pre-alert_instructions:_ocean', 'Pre-Advice is a must, earliest, immediately after shipment and send by any communication method to our Seafreight office fax No. 62-21-8080040-41\r\ne-mail to : iswan.nizar@cardiglogistics.com, cc to : asrul@cardiglogistics.com\r\nAn advice must include complete shipping detail;\r\n\r\n\r\nOBL \r\nHBL \r\nVessel \r\nVoyage \r\nETS \r\nETA \r\nImporter name and full address / telephone , PO. Box or Bank address is not sufficient \r\nShipping agent full address in Indonesia.\r\n\r\nBack to Back Shipments \r\nShipping Document Copies must be sent by any method and received by CARDIG LOGISTICS prior to vessel\'s arrival. Master B/L as Express Bill Of Lading is recommended instead to courier original. \r\n\r\nConsolidation Shipments\r\nShipping Document Copies (complete) must be sent by any method and received by CARDIG LOGISTICS 7 working days prior to vessel\'s arrival. Master B/L as Express Bill Of lading is recommended instead to courier original. \r\n'),
(5870, 1989, 'customs_clearance', 'Indonesian Customs only receives and process the complete docs, means\r\n- Consignee Original Letter of Authority\r\n- Original Airwaybill (Master/House) \r\n- Original Invoices (means with SHIPPER\'S SIGNATURE, SHIPPER\'S COMPANY STAMP, WITH SHIPPER\'S COMPANY HEAD LETTER)\r\n- Consignee must have this following license ; SRP (Customs Registration Letter), API (Importers Identification Number) and NPWP (Company Number Tax Identification)\r\n- Cosignnee must have NPIK (for specific items), POM (for durgs and food)\r\nIt means before you send the cargo to Indonesia, make sure give us alerts in advance so we can check to the consignee whether they have the mention requirement or not.\r\n\r\nOriginal invoice means not sent by fax, not computer generated invoice, and not copies.\r\n\r\n\r\nCARDIG LOGISTICS can arrange permanent customs clearance on behalf of shipper if CARDIG LOGISTICS is mentioned as consignee and or notify party in the shipping and other documents. This mean CARDIG LOGISTICS will acting as importer and all nessesary import permit must be provided by CARDIG LOGISTICS and import duty/tax will be registered under the name and risk of CARDIG LOGISTICS. We would not recommended this practise. In normal case consignee will provide Authorizartion Letter, their Tax Registration Number and Import Lisence.\r\n\r\nAverage clearance time for air freight without physical customs inspection 1-2 days and with customs inspection 2-3 days, for sea freight without inspections 2-3 days and with inspection 3-5 days counted as working days and subject to complete documents without discrepancy(s) on the goods and document(s), to be accepted by Indonesian Authority/regulation. \r\n\r\nOriginal Commercial Invoice must be provided for customs clearance. For airfreight must be attached to the relevant Air Waybill. Failure to comply original, consignee must make a legal statement that invoice value is correct and need customs approval.Please avoid providing only copies.\r\n\r\nCertificate of Analysis is required for chemicals.\r\n\r\nSpecial permits from relevant government department / institution for telecommunication device, any kind of medicine / food / beverage (consider as commercial), and any media materials, also see Tact Rules. \r\n\r\nOriginal passport is required for removal / personal effect goods to get free import duty / tax if Indonesian citizen , plus resident and working permit if non Indonesian citizen.Please contact us before shipping this kind of cargo. \r\n'),
(5871, 1989, 'transshipment_requirements', 'Generally no transhipment facilities, cargo to be customs cleared at port/airport of destination mentioned on Master shipping document. Otherwise importer have to put guarantee 100% of total Import Duty and Tax before onforward to next Indonesian Customs port/airport. '),
