(6138, 1999, 'creating_consolidation_manifest:_air', '\"Description of Goods\" must read \"Consolidation As Per Attached Manifest\". \r\nManifest must have full name and address of both shipper and consignee. \r\nWe require the manifest at least 24 hours prior to arrival of flight so incoming cargo can be electronically reported to Customs. New legislation will come into effect from 2002 that will allow the Customs Dept to fine forwarders approx AUD 500.00 per case where incoming cargo is not reported within the required time frame. This cost will be passed on to overseas agents if they have failed to send a prealert manifest. '),
