(7662, 2055, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_mawb', 'Ocean Express CNPJ # must always be declared on consignee\'s field of MAWB. \r\nTotal amount of freight charges must be shown on MAWB\'s respective field. \r\n\"Freight As Agreed \" wording is not acceptable. It\'s considered illegal by Brazilian laws, subject to penalties. \r\nNet/Net rate must be declared on the respective field of MAWB unless it is not allowed you can mention the IATA rate. \r\nGross Weight has to be exactly the same as declared on both Commercial Invoice and Packing List.\r\nPlease declare goods description as \"Consolidation shipment as per cargo manifest\" '),
(7663, 2055, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_mb/l', 'Ocean Express CNPJ number must always be shown on consignee\'s field of MB/L. \r\nNet/net freight amount must always be shown in numbers and words. \r\nShip mode must always be shown. \r\n\"Freight as agreed\" wording is not acceptable. It\'s considered illegal by Brazilian laws.\r\nGross Weight has to be exactly the same as declared on both Commercial Invoice and Packing List.Quantity and kind of volumes / packages must be shown. '),
(7664, 2055, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_hawb', 'Importer\'s CNPJ # must always be declared on consignee\'s field of HAWB \r\nAll eventual charges/costs at origin must be declared and named as \"CHC\" or \"CHA\" on HAWB. Such charges must be added on the top of airfreight and the total amount must be declared on HAWB\'s respective field. \r\n\"Freight As Agreed\" wording is not acceptable. It\'s considered illegal by Brazilian laws. \r\nSelling rate must be always declared on HAWB\'s respective field. \r\nThe original # 2 of the HAWB must always be included in the set of documents accompanying the cargo to the destination. Brazilian Customs will not allow the clearance of the goods without this original. \r\nAlso, commercial invoice and packing list of goods which must accompany the cargo must be an original draft, signed. Photocopies with an \"original\" stamp are not acceptable. \r\nBefore delivering cargo to airline, please always fax us copies of MAWB and HAWB for our approval. We should also receive the complete schedule / flight details. \r\nBesides, receiving the intended flight confirmation, we must also receive the confirmation that the shipment really took place according to previous schedule. \r\nEvery single package, carton or skid must bear a label identifying goods as per data shown on MAWB and HAWB. \r\nPlease make sure you to send following documents together with cargo: \r\n- MAWB original, original and non-negotiable copies have to be stamped and signed\r\n- HAWB original 2, original and non negotiable copies have to be stamped and signed\r\n- cargo manifest - original stamped and signed\r\n- commercial invoice - original stamped and signed\r\n- packing list - original stamped and signed\r\n- agent\'s invoice.\r\nGross weight has to be exactly the same weight as MAWB, commercial Invoice and Packing List.'),
(7665, 2055, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_hb/l', 'Importer\'s CNPJ # must always be shown on consignee\'s field of HB/L \r\n\"Freight as agreed\" wording is not acceptable. It\'s considered illegal by Brazilian laws. \r\nHB/L and MB/L must always show same issue date. \r\nSelling rate must always be shown on HB/L respective field. All other charges must be added to the ocean freight amount, and everything declared as Total Freight Charges. Do not break down charges. \r\nShip mode ( FCL/FCL or LCL/LCL ) must always be shown. \r\nAny other charge the shipment may have MUST be printed on HBL. If not mentioned, consignee cannot remmit the money out of Brazil. \r\nBefore actual shipment, please always fax or scan us copies of MBL and HBL for our approval. \r\nWe must also receive the complete schedule details 9ETD, ETA, Vessel, Voyage). \r\nBesides shipment pre-advice, we will need a shipment confirmation after vessel\'s departure. \r\nWe need that you send us via courier at least 05 days after vessel\'s departure to do the desconsolidation and Customs Clearance: \r\n- MB/L - 02 originals + non negotiable copies, original and non-negotiable copies have to be stamped and signed\r\n- HBL - 02 originals + non negotiable copies, original and non-negotiable copies have to be stamped and signed\r\n- Cargo Manifest - 01 original - stamped and signed\r\n- Packing list - 01 original - stamped and signed\r\n- agent\'s invoice (credit / debit note)\r\nGross Weight has to be exactly the same weight as on MBL, Commercial Invoice and Packing List. Quantity and kind of volumes / packages must be shown.'),
(7666, 2055, 'pre-alert_instructions:_air', 'Before actual shipment, please always e-mail (fretes@oceanexpress.com.br) or fax us copies of MAWB & HAWB for our approval. We should also receive the complete shipment schedule/flight details.'),
