(7688, 2056, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_mb/l', '- Pls ask ocean carrier to issue it as Seaway bill or Telex Release, originals are not required. Printed at destination also is not necessary, always to release it under copy terms.\r\n- Originals always delays releasing and might cause demurrages or storages.'),
(7689, 2056, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_hawb', '- HAWB can be rated or \"As Agreed\" \r\n- Pls show if freight is prepaid or collect. \r\n- Pls show if charges are prepaid or collect. \r\n- Original #2 (for cnee) must come inside a pouch.\r\n- Credits and debits must be sent inside the consolidation document pouch.'),
(7690, 2056, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_hb/l', '- HB/L can be rated or \"As Agreed\" \r\n- Express release is allowed by Mexican customs.\r\n- Credits and debits must be sent inside the consolidation document pouch.\r\n- If HB/L is requested by shipper to be issue as original, they most be delivered to shipper as well as all other documents related to shipment.\r\n- If HB/L is requested by shipper to be issue as Telex Release or Surrender, a copy must be provided to shipper and he must sent a copy to copnsignee, since we will require a copy to be duly endorsed in order to release it.\r\n- If HB/L changes from original to Surrender or Telex Release, then a copy with statement of \"Telex Release\" or \"Surrender\" must be provided to MAC as well as shipper, since we will require a copy to be duly endorsed in order to release it.'),
(7691, 2056, 'pre-alert_instructions:_air', '- Pre-Alerts should be complete and include a copy of the MAWB, HAWB, commercial invoice and packing list, if available.\r\n- Pre-alert must be sent to mexia@macargo.com.mx'),
(7692, 2056, 'pre-alert_instructions:_ocean', '- Pre-Alerts should be complete and include a copy of the MAWB, HAWB, commercial invoice and packing list, if available.\r\n- Pre-alert must be sent to mexocean@macargo.com.mx '),
(7693, 2056, 'customs_clearance', '- Pls be advised that Mexico Air Cargo Systems,  S.A. de C.V. cannot act as importer/exporter of record.\r\n- No foreign company is allowed to be importer/exporter of record.\r\n- A mexican company must be duly registered as importer/exporter and have a valid import license in order clear shipment on their behalf.\r\n- In order to clear shipment, importer/exporter must provide a Customs Power of Attorney in order to submit the entry on their behalf. If a Power of Attorney has been issued to another broker, then the cargo will be turned over to that broker for clearance. \r\n- Importer/Exporter must provide ALL legal documents that proves they are legally established in Mexico, otherwise our customs broker will reject to clear shipment without any law enforcement.'),
(7694, 2056, 'transshipment_requirements', '- Transhipment are not handled by MAC. Mexican Law has too many locks in order to make clearance almost impossible. Expenses will be extrenmely high and also will be extrenmely delayed at Customs.'),
(7695, 2056, 'legal_requirements_with_regards_to_commercial_invoices,_certificates_of_origin,_etc.', '- Original commercial invoices are not required by customs in order to consignee can clear cargo. \r\n- Shipper must always send them to consignee, we are not responsible for any document sent by courier or pouch.\r\n- Certificates are required only when requested by consignee, so they are responsible for approving or issuing documents based on nature of goods.'),
(7696, 2056, 'dangerous_goods_requirements', '- Some DGR goods might not accepted by Mexican Customs or have special requirements, which should be checked in advance by shipper/consignee (before shipping out).\r\n- A copy of the DG Certificate or IMO and/or MSDS sheets must accompany shipments.'),
(7697, 2056, 'special_instructions', '-  ALL pieces for air or ocean shipments must be properly labeled in order to avoid problems/delays and extra expenses.\r\n- DDU/DDP shipments please do not ship out without our approval, pls contact us in advance. If shipment is shipped out without notifying about it and arrabnge all prior to ship, MAC will not be resposible for any extracost or mishandling on it.\r\n- Any quotation approved for DDU/DDP shipment by Agent must be fully paid, more even if quotation is estimated based on information provided or in case of any problem or delay on clearance, pick up, freight or any part of logistics.\r\n- Pls be advsied that Mexican regulation just allows to do payments or receive payment in USD as foreign currency, any other are not recognize and we cannot set up payment on them. Agent is responsible to provide invoice, debite or credit note in USD considering to protect exchange rate good enough in order to prevent any shortage or loss in shipment. Also, bank intermediary fees needs to be considered by Agent and on its account.\r\n- Any Fines or Penalties for mishandling, lack of documents, lack of pre-alert or following, will be on account of Agent. Certanly we will support in order to minimize extra expenses or fines, but definitely on account of Agent.'),
