(8529, 2087, 'creating_consolidation_manifest:_ocean', 'Manifest should be specific and include the following: \r\n\r\nMB/L NUMBER \r\nHB/L NUMBER \r\nPIECES AND WEIGHT \r\nSHIPPER AND CONSIGNEE (of HB/Ls)\r\nVESSEL AND VOYAGE\r\nCONTAINER NUMBER \r\nGOODS DESCRIPTION (Must be the same as HB/L)\r\n'),
(8530, 2087, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_mawb', 'Please use standard IATA instructions for issuing AWB'),
(8531, 2087, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_mb/l', 'B/Ls used in shipments to/from the US, must be FMC bonded Bills of Lading.  All Steamship Lines calling US Ports will be FMC bonded.  '),
(8532, 2087, 'pre-alert_instructions:_air', 'Pre-Alerts should be complete and should include a copy of the Master, House Bill(s), along with a copy of any commercial documentation and packing slips.  Please see the local office shipping instructions for the email/fax numbers to send pre-alert to.  '),
(8533, 2087, 'pre-alert_instructions:_ocean', 'Pre-Alerts should be complete and should include a copy of the Master, House Bill(s), along with a copy of any commercial documentation and packing slips.  Please see the local office shipping instructions for the email/fax numbers to send pre-alert to.  '),
(8534, 2087, 'customs_clearance', 'Cargo Brokers can do customs clearance for any air and ocean shipments. However, a Power of Attorney is required in order to clear Customs for any importer/shipper. If a Power of Attorney has been issued to another broker, then the cargo will be turned over to that broker for clearance. \r\n\r\nA Power of Attorney form is available on the Cargo Brokers website (www.cargobrokers.com).  \r\n'),
(8535, 2087, 'transshipment_requirements', 'Terminate Master Bill at the local CBI Port (ATL, CLT, or MIA).  \r\nThe House Bill should terminate at the final destination (the port to which CBI will forward the shipment.  \r\n'),
