(8780, 2096, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_hawb', 'Please use standard IATA instructions for issuing AWB. HAWB should indicate actual description of cargo, not a general classification(Example: \r\n\"Aircraft parts\" or \"Spare Parts\" are NOT acceptable, but instead the HB/L should state \"Nozzle, Aircraft Part\" or \"Engine Piston\").'),
(8781, 2096, 'instructions_for_issuance_of_a_hb/l', 'HB/L should indicate actual description of cargo not a general classification. Example: \"Air Craft Parts\" or \"Spare Parts\" are NOT acceptable, but instead the HB/L should state: \"Nozzle, \"Aircraft Parts \" or \"Engine Piston\". B/Ls used in shipments to/from the US, must be FMC Bonded Bil of Lading. * If your company does not have an FMC bond, you can use a co-loaded / NVOCC with an FMC bond, or you may contact Carsten Steinmetz at CBI to discuss the possibility of using CBI Bills of Lading.  '),
(8782, 2096, 'pre-alert_instructions:_air', 'Pre-alerts should be complete and should include a copy of the Master.  House Bill(s), along wit a copy of any commercial documentation and packing slip.  Pre-alerts should be sent to htfnchsimport@cargobrokers.com.'),
(8783, 2096, 'pre-alert_instructions:_ocean', 'Pre-alerts should be complete and should include a copy of a Master,House Bill(s) along with a copy of any commercial documentation and packing slip.  Pre-alerts should be sent to htfnchsimport@cargobrokers.com  '),
(8784, 2096, 'customs_clearance', 'We can do customs clearance for any air and ocean shipments.  However, a Power of Attorney is required in order to clear Customs for any importer/shipper.  If a Power of Attorney has been issued to another broker, then the cargo will be turned over to the broker for clearance.  A Power of Attorney form is available on the Cargo Brokers website: (www.cargobrokers.com).   '),
(8785, 2096, 'transshipment_requirements', 'Terminate Master Bill at the local CBI Port (ATL,CHS,CLT,MIA). The House Bill should terminate at the final destination the port to which CBI will forward the shipment.'),
