(425, 1, '2018-03-15 17:22:52', '2018-03-15 17:22:52', 'Interamerica Group specializes in transportation around the world and are available at all times in order to meet the requirements of transport needs in whatever forms. Interamerica Group\'s expert staff coordinates cargo through the complex world of international trade. Offering International Marine, Air, Inland, FCL and LCL services for all types of cargo including Hazardous. Additional services include warehousing, Customs clearance, insurance, tracking and project cargo. Interamerica Group strives for excellence and quality service maintaining constant communication with customers in an effective and efficient manner. Standing by their mission of providing a flexible service of high quality, reliable and efficient, in order to achieve customer satisfaction and contribute to the success of their customers business.\r\n\r\nCongratulations Interamerica Group for joining the HTFN family and its list of prestigious members!\r\n\r\nFor more information regarding Interamerica Group Paraguay please go to http://www.interamerica.com.py', 'HTFN Welcomes Its Newest Member!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '423-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-03-15 17:22:52', '2018-03-15 17:22:52', '', 423, 'http://dev.htfn.com/423-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(426, 1, '2018-03-15 17:30:43', '2018-03-15 17:30:43', 'HTFN Netherlands, KDS Cargo, recently faced two insurance issues regarding shipments handled in cooperation with another HTFN-partner. One shipment was damaged in the harbor, the other shipment was lost at destination (found after consignee ordered a replacement, so in the end consignee received double product).\r\n\r\nIn both cases, neither KDS nor the HTFN-partner was to blame, but because the respective consignees had not arranged insurance, it became a big issue. Because this happens all too often KDS wants to emphasize the importance of transport insurance and suggests to everyone to always talk to their customers about this issue. It is not that KDS is in the business of pushing the sales of insurance but think it is important to take good care of customers and considers part of their job is informing and advising customers about the need of insurance.\r\n\r\nIt might also be important to mention a recent article in \"The Loadstar\" quoting in part, \"According to this LinkedIn blog by Steve Fodor, director at the US-based Association For Trade Compliance, 90% of US-bound cargo moves without any insurance coverage. Mr. Foder\'s knowledge stems from 33 years working in international trade, and he cites three of the most common reasons (or excuses) given by shippers who regularly do not insure their cargo.....(1) Customers assume business insurance covers cargo, Most insurance policies do not cover cargo in transit (2) They assume their suppliers cover the cargo, Since most products are purchased on an FOB basis the supplier is not required to provide insurance coverage (3) Nothing bad has ever happened, Just because you have not had any past problems do you want to risk losing tens of thousands of dollars just to avoid paying a small insurance premium...risky.\"\r\n\r\nKDS respectfully sends a reminder to those considering insurance for their cargo, failure to insure is risky business!', 'HTFN Netherlands Cautions Uninsured Cargo Is Risky Business!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'htfn-netherlands-cautions-uninsured-cargo-is-risky-business', '', '', '2018-03-15 17:31:38', '2018-03-15 17:31:38', '', 0, 'http://dev.htfn.com/?p=426', 0, 'post', '', 0),
